quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  3,186,"You ˹believers˺ will surely be tested in your wealth and yourselves, and you will certainly hear many hurtful words from those who were given the Scripture before you and ˹from˺ the polytheists. But if you are patient and mindful ˹of God˺—surely this is a resolve to aspire to"
  3,187,"˹Remember, O Prophet,˺ when God took the covenant of those who were given the Scripture to make it known to people and not hide it, yet they cast it behind their backs and traded it for a fleeting gain. What a miserable profit"
  3,188,Do not let those who rejoice in their misdeeds and love to take credit for what they have not done think they will escape torment. They will suffer a painful punishment
  3,189,To God ˹alone˺ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. And God is Most Capable of everything
  3,190,"Indeed, in the creation of the heavens and the earth and the alternation of the day and night there are signs for people of reason"
  3,191,"˹They are˺ those who remember God while standing, sitting, and lying on their sides, and reflect on the creation of the heavens and the earth ˹and pray˺, “Our Lord! You have not created ˹all of˺ this without purpose. Glory be to You! Protect us from the torment of the Fire"
  3,192,"Our Lord! Indeed, those You commit to the Fire will be ˹completely˺ disgraced! And the wrongdoers will have no helpers"
  3,193,"Our Lord! We have heard the caller to ˹true˺ belief, ˹proclaiming,˺ ‘Believe in your Lord ˹alone˺,’ so we believed. Our Lord! Forgive our sins, absolve us of our misdeeds, and allow us ˹each˺ to die as one of the virtuous"
  3,194,Our Lord! Grant us what You have promised us through Your messengers and do not put us to shame on Judgment Day—for certainly You never fail in Your promise.”
  3,195,"So their Lord responded to them: “I will never deny any of you—male or female—the reward of your deeds. Both are equal in reward. Those who migrated or were expelled from their homes, and were persecuted for My sake and fought and ˹some˺ were martyred—I will certainly forgive their sins and admit them into Gardens under which rivers flow, as a reward from God. And with God is the finest reward!”"
  3,196,Do not be deceived by the prosperity of the disbelievers throughout the land
  3,197,It is only a brief enjoyment. Then Hell will be their home—what an evil place to rest
  3,198,"But those who are mindful of their Lord will be in Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there forever—as an accommodation from God. And what is with God is best for the virtuous"
  3,199,"Indeed, there are some among the People of the Book who truly believe in God and what has been revealed to you ˹believers˺ and what was revealed to them. They humble themselves before God—never trading God’s revelations for a fleeting gain. Their reward is with their Lord. Surely God is swift in reckoning"
  3,200,"O believers! Patiently endure, persevere, stand on guard, and be mindful of God, so you may be successful"